# Lambdas (what2play-services)

## Layout

- **npm workspaces** rooted at `lambdas/package.json`. Install and test from **`lambdas/`**: `npm ci` and `npm test`.
- One folder per function (`what2play-*`). Commit **`lambdas/package-lock.json`** so CI can `npm ci`.

## Tests

- Jest discovers **`**/*.test.js`**. Prefer unit tests for pure logic in `lib/` (and `what2play-lists/lib/cache.js`).
- **`jest.mock('./routes', () => ({ ... }))`** factories must only use **`jest.fn()`** or literals — do not reference outer variables (Jest hoisting restriction).
- Handler tests mock `@aws-sdk/client-dynamodb` and `@aws-sdk/lib-dynamodb` plus `./routes` as needed.

## CI packaging

- **`terraform-deploy.yml`** zips each Lambda and runs **`npm install --production`** inside each package directory. Changing workspace layout may affect what lands in the zip; verify deploy artifacts if you restructure dependencies.

## Optional extraction

- When index-level logic is hard to test (e.g. caching), extract small modules under `lib/` rather than duplicating logic in tests.
